Im sorry if i have hurt u in any way. I dont mean to. If u think something bad about me then thats ur opinion i respect that but dont be surprised if u see a tear in my eye. I just want to say that not everything in life goes as planned and you cant just ignore the way life takes you. life takes you places sometimes it somewhere you might not expect. but in the end everything works out for itself. you may end up with different friends later on no matter how hard you try to hold onto them. but there are the select few that you will stay friends with for the rest of your life and i am truly greatful for them. i would be no where without them. so again i say to you..if i have ever done anything to you i didnt do it intentionally and i am truly sorry for any pain i have caused you. i just hope that you can find it in your heart to forgive me. please look at me differently and try to see it from my perspective as well and if you still think the same way then by all means think it. im sorry for everything you know who you guys are.

so adam's entry got me thinkin....if you wanna know more read the cut....

 

"know that in 7-8 years i will not even have the faintest idea as to what these people are doing. i worry about that quite a bit " that quote from adams journal is what got me thinkin.

Here we are complaining about school and stuff everyday. " aww i gotta go to school"" aww i got practice" we complain so much we fail to realize all the memories we could be making in just that one day. We need to cherish every moment that we have with our friends in high school because more than likely you wont be friends with a lot of those people after high school. You'll all go to different colleges and slowly lose contact. At every moment of the day you're making a memory. So next time you complain about going somewhere or doing something just think about the things that could happen that are great. The greatest memories come from things unplanned.  Just hanging out with a few close friends just watching a movie and talking can mean so much. Every little thing like that with your friends is something special and you'll remember that when you're older.

So the point of this entry was.... Never take for granted the times you have with your friends because they're special. Love a lot. Laugh until your stomach hurts. Take walks on the beach. Stay home on the weekend and  watch a movie with the girls. Be crazy.  Sing your heart out once in a while. When you're in love shout it to the world. Be yourself. Never let anyone change you. Pour your heart into everything you do. And Most of all take every moment of your life and put in your heart and let it stay!!!

<3<3<3 Britt
